Financial metrics temporarily unavailable (rate limited) - 2025-09-24

Title   : Bajaj Electricals acquire Morphy Richard’s brand rights 
Source  : www.thehindubusinessline.com
Published: 2025-09-24T12:42:04
Fetched : 2025-09-24T17:28:24.068399
URL     : https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/companies/bajaj-electricals-acquire-morphy-richards-brand-rights/article70088877.ece
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Bajaj Electricals has announced the acquisition of the intellectual property rights of Morphy Richards for ₹146 crore in India, Nepal, Bhutan, Bangladesh, Sri Lanka and the Maldives.
The consumer durable maker will acquire the rights from Irish maker Glen Electric Limited (part of the Glen Dimplex Group).
“We wish to inform you that the Board of Directors of the Company has given its consent to a proposal for the acquisition of the ‘Morphy Richards’ brand and related intellectual property rights (“Business IP” / “MR Brand”) in the territories of India, Nepal, Bhutan, Bangladesh, the Maldives, and Sri Lanka (“Territory”), from Glen Electric Limited (part of the Glen Dimplex Group, Ireland), the owner of the MR Brand/Business IP, for a consideration of INR 146 crore (exclusive of any taxes/duties, etc. payable in the Territory) (the “Transaction”). This Transaction will be subject to negotiation and execution of definitive agreements between the parties and the receipt of necessary statutory and regulatory approvals, as applicable,” the company informed the stock exchanges.
Earlier, Bajaj Electricals had acquired cookware brand Nirlep Appliances for a consideration of ₹42.50 crore.
Published on September 24, 2025

