Title   : Midcap Momentum: 7 stocks reporting rising EPS for 4 consecutive quarters 
Source  : economictimes.indiatimes.com
Published: 2025-09-24T10:31:01
Fetched : 2025-09-24T18:13:32.079009
URL     : https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/markets/stocks/news/midcap-momentum-7-stocks-reporting-rising-eps-for-4-consecutive-quarters/slideshow/124090329.cms
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7 NSE Midcaps Post EPS Growth for 4 Straight Quarters
Consistently increasing quarterly earnings per share (EPS) indicates that a company is improving its profitability over time. This trend suggests strong financial health, effective management strategies, and potential for sustainable growth. In the NSE midcap segment, seven companies have notably improved their EPS, showing increases for four consecutive quarters (till the June '25 quarter) compared to the previous quarter, according to profitability scan data from StockEdge.com.
Agencies
2/8
Hexaware Technologies
Hexaware Technologies recorded an EPS of Rs 6.25 in the June quarter of 2025, up from Rs 4.54 in the same period last year.
Agencies
3/8
Coforge
Coforge posted an EPS of Rs 9.49 in the June quarter of 2025, increasing from Rs 3.99 in the corresponding quarter of the previous year.
Agencies
4/8
Indian Overseas Bank
Indian Overseas Bank reported an EPS of Rs 0.61 for the June quarter of 2025, rising from Rs 0.34 in the same quarter last year
ETMarkets.com
5/8
Muthoot Finance
Muthoot Finance announced an EPS of Rs 50.22 in the June quarter of 2025, up from Rs 28.99 in the equivalent period last year.
Agencies
6/8
Hero MotoCorp
Hero MotoCorp declared an EPS of Rs 85.26 for the June quarter of 2025, an increase from Rs 52.31 in the same quarter the previous year.
Agencies
7/8
Yes Bank
Yes Bank recorded an EPS of Rs 0.26 in the June quarter of 2025, higher than Rs 0.16 reported in the corresponding quarter last year.
Agencies
8/8
Persistent Systems
Persistent Systems posted an EPS of Rs 27.17 in the June quarter of 2025, up from Rs 19.89 in the same quarter last year.

